      <p>pvl, that&#39;s a good question!  I&#39;ve heard from many sources over the years that salting beans makes them tough, but I&#39;ve not found it to be true, and America&#39;s Test Kitchen (the people who produce the magazine Cook&#39;s Illustrated) made a great video that explains their findings on the matter.  I&#39;ve added a link to the video and some of my own thoughts in the recipe headnotes above.</p>
