    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Alas, I did not have a hambone in my freezer (used it up for lentil soup, yum yum). BUT I did have some slab bacon, and some frozen cooked shell beans from the garden and some ditto kale because it&#39;s what we eat all winter, and some of the last sweet post-frost harvested carrots&#8230;. so thanks to your post, a bunch of Vermonters who are not-so-revelling in sub-zero wind chill for the first time had a yummy, warming, creamy, delicious dinner. And the youngest member of our family (2) shoveled it in with glee and asked for more. Twice! Thanks for the inspiration!<br /> (PS I added some par-cooked farro near the end and that added some good rib-sticking grainy goodness).</p>
    </div>

